      "role": "user",
      "content": "I see. So even if those specific studies are criticized, there's still a lot of discussion about how these biological markers might explain the gaps. If we were to look at the data from a purely statistical standpoint, without the \"social\" lens, what are the strongest arguments proponents make for why these disparities exist across different populations? Like, what's the \"essentialist\" view on why certain racial groups tend to cluster in certain cognitive or socioeconomic tiers?",
